[{"id":"49160f542f229f2f2316e4fa960a8b45","from":"Petra Nemcova","from_email":"petranemcova@happyheartsfund.org","to":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","to_list":[{"name":"jeeproject@yahoo.com","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"10 YEAR ANNIVERSARY HAPPY HEARTS FUND GALA.","date":"2014-05-08T00:49:16.000Z","formatted_date":"May 8, 2014","formatted_time":"12:49 AM","body":"Hi sunshine,\n\nHope you are having Happy week. Here is the invitation to the Happy Hearts Gala on June 19th, which this year will be very special and meaningful.\n\nIt is hard to believe that this year marks the 10th anniversary of the devastating 2004 tsunami which I was blessed to survive, therefore it will be an extra special gala. We will celebrate the 85 resilient disaster-proof schools that have been rebuilt and the happiness that they have brought to 46,000 children in seven countries that have been impacted by natural disasters. Our goal is to open our 100th school by December 26th 2014, on the day of the anniversary.\n\nThis night will also be extremely special because of our incredible honorees. Bill Clinton, the 42nd President of United States, will.i.am (http://will.i.am/)  and apl.de.ap from the Black Eyed Peas and United Airlines. Each of our honorees focus on helping children and communities after natural disasters. I have attached the invitation for you below.\n\nWill you be able to join us during this meaningful and unforgettable event please? Will you help us to rebuild 100 resilient disaster-proof schools this year for children who are forgotten for years after natural disasters? Would you help us to bring hope to children who lost it as their voices have not been heard please?\n\nLots of Love, Light and Laughter\nP.\nhttp://vimeo.com/87591486\n\n\n** INVITATION\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n** Happy Hearts Fund Gala\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n\n** Celebrating the achievements we have created together 10 years after the Indian Ocean Tsunami.\n------------------------------------------------------------\nLifetime Achievement Award Honoree\n\n\n** BILL CLINTON\n------------------------------------------------------------\nFOUNDER OF THE CLINTON FOUNDATION\n& 42nd PRESIDENT OF THE UNITED STATES\nFor his leadership and life saving work ensuring that children and communities are not forgotten after disaster strikes\n\nHonored Partner Award Honoree\n\n\n** UNITED AIRLINES\n------------------------------------------------------------\nMR. JEFF SMISEK, CHAIRMAN OF THE BOARD, PRESIDENT & CEO\nFor their continued support and partnership enabling HHF team members to conduct important site visits to the countries and schools that we support\n\nSpirit Award Honoree\n\n\n** APL.DE.AP & WILL.I.AM\n------------------------------------------------------------\nFor utilizing their talents and showing commitment to children and communities impacted by natural disasters in the Philippines and other countries\n\nWith special music appearances\n\n\n** Thursday June 19th 2014\n------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n** Cipriani 42nd Street, New York\n------------------------------------------------------------\nCocktails at 6pm, Dinner and Program at 7:00pm\n\nClick here (http://r20.rs6.net/tn.jsp?e=001obvX3vDNyq1oYE--JUYMTB8Wxh7pm81BerYk6DNUtpfa6rKxhnnWcbUPNX4QllL4R735y5t5v8LFfQbbR8v2O7EMVTV7X79Sv13-UEuj03o=)  to see the impact that your support has made!\n\nTo become a sponsor or purchase tables/tickets, please contact:\nSue Veres Royal at\nor sue@happyheartsfund.org (mailto:sue@happyheartsfund.org)\n\nThe mission of Happy Hearts Fund is to rebuild schools and restore hope and opportunity in the lives of children after natural disasters. We work during the period after emergency response is complete, implementing sustainable practices to ensure a lasting impact.\n\nGlobally, Happy Hearts Fund is active in seven countries and has built/rebuilt 85 schools\nand kindergartens. Since inception in 2006, our programs have benefitted more than 46,000 children and 490,000 community members.\n\nwww.happyheartsfund.org (http://www.happyheartsfund.org/)\n\n============================================================\nCopyright \u00a9 2014 Happy Hearts Fund, All rights reserved.\n You are receiving this email because you have requested information from Happy Hearts Fund.\n\nOur mailing address is:\nHappy Hearts Fund\nPO Box 725\nNew York, NY 10014\nUSA\n** unsubscribe from this list (http://happyheartsfund.us2.list-manage.com/unsubscribe?u=c80ab18b6ed45d0c817ea32b1&id=db4e8e7542&e=1835002b47&c=14855f8801)\n** update subscription preferences (http://happyheartsfund.us2.list-manage1.com/profile?u=c80ab18b6ed45d0c817ea32b1&id=db4e8e7542&e=1835002b47)","body_html":"<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Strict//EN\" \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-strict.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n    <head>\n    \t<!-- NAME: 1 COLUMN -->\n        <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n        <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0\">\n        <title>10 YEAR ANNIVERSARY HAPPY HEARTS FUND GALA.</title>\n\n        <!--[if gte mso 6]>\n        <style>\n            table.mcnFollowContent {width:100% !important;}\n            table.mcnShareContent {width:100% !important;}\n        </style>\n        <![endif]-->\n    <style type=\"text/css\">\n\t\tbody,#bodyTable,#bodyCell{\n\t\t\theight:100% !important;\n\t\t\tmargin:0;\n\t\t\tpadding:0;\n\t\t\twidth:100% !important;\n\t\t}\n\t\ttable{\n\t\t\tborder-collapse:collapse;\n\t\t}\n\t\timg,a img{\n\t\t\tborder:0;\n\t\t\toutline:none;\n\t\t\ttext-decoration:none;\n\t\t}\n\t\th1,h2,h3,h4,h5,h6{\n\t\t\tmargin:0;\n\t\t\tpadding:0;\n\t\t}\n\t\tp{\n\t\t\tmargin:1em 0;\n\t\t\tpadding:0;\n\t\t}\n\t\ta{\n\t\t\tword-wrap:break-word;\n\t\t}\n\t\t.ReadMsgBody{\n\t\t\twidth:100%;\n\t\t}\n\t\t.ExternalClass{